The paper deals with physical-layer security in cognitive radio networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses multiuser scheduling, which falls under the category of communication networks (cs.CR). The use of artificial noise to improve security is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and the overall system design and optimization can be considered as a system and control theory (cs.SY) problem.
